features: Efficient Organization: Stay organized with our premium accordion file folder featuring 5 pockets and 5 tabs. It provides ample space (up to 250 sheets) to categorize and store your important documents, ensuring easy access and efficient organization.

Secure and Durable: Crafted with high-quality materials, our accordion file folder is built to last. The sturdy construction and snap closure ensure the safety and longevity of your documents, providing reliable protection against wear and tear.

Letter Size Compatibility: Designed to accommodate letter-sized papers, this expanding file organizer ensures that all your important documents fit perfectly, eliminating the need for folding or creasing.

Easy File Identification: The included classification labels enable you to label and identify each section of the file folder effortlessly. This feature allows for efficient sorting and quick retrieval of specific documents, saving you valuable time and effort.

Stylish Design: With its sleek colors, our file folder adds a touch of elegance to your workspace. The professional and modern design enhances your professional image while keeping your documents well-organized.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Organize with Ease!
reviews.reviewText: As someone with a full-time job and multiple side businesses, managing the influx of loose papers has always been a challenge. Enter the 5-Tab Expanding File Folder – a game-changer in my quest for organization and efficiency.What stands out immediately is the generous number of tabs that come with the folder. This feature is a lifesaver for someone like me who needs the flexibility to rename and categorize different sections efficiently. It's like having a personalized filing system that adapts to the evolving needs of my various projects.The material used in the file folder is impressively strong and durable. The sturdiness ensures that my important documents are well-protected, even when the folder is filled to capacity. It's a reassuring feeling to know that my papers are secure and won't be easily damaged.Another aspect I appreciate is the reusability of the file folder. In a world where sustainability matters, being able to reuse this folder for future projects is a significant plus. The quality of the material ensures that it can withstand repeated use, making it a reliable and eco-friendly choice.The fact that the 5-Tab Expanding File Folder comes in a 2-pack is the icing on the cake. It provides excellent value for money, giving me not just one, but two reliable solutions to keep my papers organized. Having an extra folder on hand has proven to be incredibly useful as my workload continues to grow.In conclusion, if you're a professional juggling multiple responsibilities and drowning in loose papers, the 5-Tab Expanding File Folder is a must-have. Its thoughtful design, durable material, and the convenience of a 2-pack make it an indispensable tool for staying organized in the midst of a busy schedule. Highly recommended!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Organize your papers
reviews.reviewText: I got these to help me keep papers organized in something nicer and more durable than a manila folder. I like that the labels are for dry erase markers, and therefore you can change the label over and over as needed. Unfortunately, they don't fit in the wall pockets I keep these papers in, so I need a different system for holding these durable accordion files if I want to keep them on the wall. For now I am using them to transport paperwork to and from work to keep it safe.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good for what I need
reviews.reviewText: I got this to keep all my business papers, receipts and anything that I might need for taxes in it. It’s the perfect size for what I need. Now I have a space saving place to keep my documents. The outside material is nice. It does come with some sticker labels. The price is right. I’m good with it all.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great to hold/store my yearly tax-related documents/receipts
reviews.reviewText: I keep my tax-related documents/receipts in a folder every year, and since I ran out of the folders I had been using, I gave these ones a try. The snap let you keep the folder closed so nothing falls out. And the plastic will provide some limited protection in case the folder gets wet somehow. There are 5 tabbed slots in the folder, so you can set a category for each slot. And I was able to write 2024 on the outside without the magic marker ink smudging. It also comes with 8 labels you can use for the 5 tabs (3 extras, or are the extra 3 for the back side of 3 tabs?). My only complaint is that I wish there were a couple more slots/tabs, so I could separate my tax docs/receipts even more uniquely.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewText: These are perfect for office organization, especially if you have tons of paperwork. The pockets are able to hold a good amount and I love the included tabs for labeling. I do wish it came with 3-4 extra label stickers, because if you mess up, then you don’t have any extras to use. But other than that, I’m happy with these and would recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars good tool for the one box challenge
reviews.reviewText: As I move through organizing my paperwork, and aspire towards completing the one box challenge (where all legacy/important documents are stored together in a fireproof box or safe) I am finding these expanding folders to be very useful. One of them is going to corral educational records, the other is going to be the home of various home improvement documents and I'm planning to order another set to corral various insurance documents.Not only can you label the tabs, but you can also just stick regular file folders into the different sections, which is what I'm doing right now. Absolutely worth it in my ongoing paperwork organizational process.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 13, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I got this for my teen daughter. She is starting school again doing her taxes for the first time and needs to be organized. Nice material and many slots. Good size for different sized files. Tabbed so you can organize per subject. Nice coloring and can wipe down if needed. The only thing is I never got the sticker tabs included to write per subject on the lipped tabs. It’s okay as I have other options but it wasn’t inside the folders or included anywhere. Overall my daughter likes it and it’s easy to travel with as it has a nice snap closure on the top to confirm the pages won’t fall out if they are large enough sheets.
